The methotodology of the Memory Evolutive Systems (developed with =
Jean-Paul Vanbremeersch), proposes a categorical model for multi-level, =
multi-agent, self-organized sytems, such as living cognitive systems.=20
In particular it studies decision making problems, both at the local =
level of a specific 'co-regulator' agent, and at the 'global' level of =
the interplay between the different co-regulators.=20
Cf. our book : "Memory Evolutive Systems: hierarchy, emergence, =
cognition" (Elsevier 2007) and more recent papers on my site
                               http://ehres.pagesperso-orange.fr=20

Andree Ehresmann

